02:16.080 --> 02:18.435
[♪♪♪]

02:34.120 --> 02:35.917
[♪♪♪]

02:40.120 --> 02:41.678
Is that you on the beach?

02:41.760 --> 02:44.479
- Oh, no, no, that's my, that's my mom.
- Oh.

02:44.600 --> 02:47.296
Yeah. She came to this beach when
she found out she was pregnant with me.

02:47.320 --> 02:50.835
I've never been, but, uh,
it's kind of our beach.

02:50.920 --> 02:52.433
[quiet laugh]

02:56.920 --> 02:58.069
That's my little sister.

02:58.160 --> 02:59.434
[man] Ah.

02:59.520 --> 03:02.512
[laughs]

03:02.600 --> 03:04.192
[man speaking Spanish]

03:04.280 --> 03:05.599
Um, you want
to see more photos?

03:05.680 --> 03:06.680
- I can...
- Um...

03:06.880 --> 03:12.876
[speaking Spanish]

03:12.960 --> 03:14.916
It's only for your eyes.

03:15.000 --> 03:16.513
Real. Authentic.

03:16.600 --> 03:17.794
You're right.

03:17.880 --> 03:20.519
Thank you.

03:20.600 --> 03:21.794
Sorry. I'm American.

03:21.880 --> 03:23.472
[chuckles]

03:23.560 --> 03:25.357
Not too many gringos here.

03:25.440 --> 03:27.670
- Yeah, bummer.
- Gracias a Dios.

03:27.760 --> 03:31.150
[woman laughs]

03:31.240 --> 03:33.595
♪♪ ["Walk on the Wild Side"
in Spanish, plays on radio]

03:34.920 --> 03:35.920
[phone chimes]

03:38.760 --> 03:40.796
She's not coming?

03:40.880 --> 03:42.360
- [speaks Spanish]
- Uh, my-my friend.

03:42.440 --> 03:44.078
You know, uh, mi amiga.

03:44.200 --> 03:46.111
You know, the girl we left
back at the hotel?

03:46.200 --> 03:48.077
You know,
she smelled like Don Julio...

03:48.160 --> 03:49.673
and bad choices?

03:49.760 --> 03:51.034
She always does this
to me, too.

03:51.120 --> 03:52.599
She-she just,
she just disappears.

03:52.680 --> 03:53.896
She's like
the-the-the fantasmo, no?

03:53.920 --> 03:55.717
You know, you know fantasmo?

03:55.800 --> 03:58.234
- Fantasma, con "A."
- Sí, con "A."

03:58.320 --> 04:00.056
The whole reason I planned
to come on this trip,

04:00.080 --> 04:02.355
con "A," was-was-was
to find the secret beach.

04:02.440 --> 04:04.112
And now she's just stuck back
at Las Rocas

04:04.200 --> 04:05.235
with the Irish flu.

04:05.320 --> 04:07.117
[sighs]

04:07.200 --> 04:08.918
[speaking Spanish]
Nursing a hangover.

04:10.560 --> 04:15.111
Sí. Major hangover.
[continues in Spanish]

04:18.560 --> 04:19.736
You-you don't like it
when someone

04:19.760 --> 04:20.875
change your plans, do you?

04:20.959 --> 04:22.757
No, I don't.

04:22.840 --> 04:24.353
No, I don't,
it's just, you know.

04:24.440 --> 04:25.509
It's not fair.

04:25.600 --> 04:26.749
Ooh, you know why, though?

04:26.840 --> 04:28.239
It's because I'm reliable.

04:28.320 --> 04:29.594
- You know "reliable"?
- Uh...

04:30.280 --> 04:32.032
"Reliable."
[speaking Spanish] Bossy.

04:33.360 --> 04:36.238
Um, I am re-li-able.

04:36.320 --> 04:38.072
[electronic voice
speaks Spanish]

04:38.160 --> 04:39.176
[speaking Spanish]
Yes, bossy.

04:39.200 --> 04:40.872
[repeats in Spanish]

04:40.960 --> 04:44.111
That's me.
[speaks Spanish] Very bossy.

04:54.040 --> 04:55.189
Hey, um...

04:55.280 --> 04:56.713
what is this beach called?

04:59.360 --> 05:00.509
You're not gonna tell me.

05:00.600 --> 05:02.158
Cool.

05:02.280 --> 05:03.315
Cool. Frio.

05:03.400 --> 05:05.356
[speaks Spanish]

05:05.440 --> 05:06.793
Not possible.

05:06.880 --> 05:08.313
It's too hot here.

05:08.400 --> 05:10.516
No, no, you're cool.
You're being cool.

05:10.600 --> 05:12.200
- Oh, never mind, that's good.
- [laughs]

05:12.280 --> 05:14.396
All right, I got it.

05:19.320 --> 05:21.151
♪♪ [bright, jazzy music
plays over radio]

05:28.640 --> 05:29.755
Is this the one?

05:31.760 --> 05:33.352
Sí.

05:51.520 --> 05:52.520
[♪♪♪]

05:53.960 --> 05:56.269
[gull screeching]

06:14.600 --> 06:17.034
This is paradise.

06:17.120 --> 06:19.315
Yeah. It's perfect.

06:25.560 --> 06:26.788
Uh...

06:26.880 --> 06:28.598
[speaking Spanish]
This is the island

06:28.680 --> 06:31.478
of the pregnant woman. No?

06:31.560 --> 06:32.560
La isla?

06:32.640 --> 06:33.640
No.

06:33.720 --> 06:35.119
[speaking Spanish]
Yes.

06:35.200 --> 06:39.352
The nose... the breasts...
and her stomach.

06:39.440 --> 06:40.668
[chuckling]
No.

06:40.760 --> 06:42.591
[woman chuckles]

06:42.680 --> 06:44.272
[speaking Spanish]
Yes, it is for me.

07:02.480 --> 07:04.118
Gracias.

07:04.200 --> 07:05.200
Gracias, señor, um...

07:05.720 --> 07:07.096
- No, no, no. Por favor.
- No, please.

07:07.120 --> 07:08.394
Please. Please, I insist.

07:08.480 --> 07:10.198
No, no, we were going
the same way.

07:10.280 --> 07:12.316
I live close by,
so... don't worry.

07:12.400 --> 07:13.879
Oh, are you sure?

07:13.960 --> 07:16.076
- Yes.
- Okay. Well, thank you.

07:16.160 --> 07:18.754
You're welcome.

07:18.840 --> 07:20.353
I'm Nancy.

07:20.440 --> 07:22.351
- Carlos. Charlie.
- Nice to meet you, Charlie.

07:22.440 --> 07:23.714
Nice to meet you.

07:23.800 --> 07:25.153
[speaking Spanish]

07:25.240 --> 07:27.800
Um, you know,
have, high school.

07:27.880 --> 07:29.154
You're in school?

07:29.240 --> 07:30.240
No.

07:30.280 --> 07:31.838
I mean,
I was in medical school,

07:31.920 --> 07:33.876
but we didn't have
Spanish there, just cadavers.

07:33.960 --> 07:36.394
I'll shut up now.
[laughs quietly]

07:36.480 --> 07:38.550
Okay, uh,
dark in a few hours, so...

07:38.640 --> 07:40.517
Oh, I never surf at night.

07:40.600 --> 07:42.158
And, uh, how you

07:42.240 --> 07:43.719
getting out from here?

07:43.800 --> 07:45.199
Uber.

07:45.280 --> 07:46.759
Who is Uber?

07:46.840 --> 07:48.831
Never mind.
Thank you, Carlos.

07:48.920 --> 07:50.353
Thank you again
for taking me here.

07:50.440 --> 07:52.396
It means a lot to me.

07:52.480 --> 07:53.640
- Okay.
- Uh, what did you say

07:53.680 --> 07:54.816
the name of it
was again, though?

07:54.840 --> 07:57.115
I just forgot,
for some reason.

07:57.200 --> 07:59.156
[speaking Spanish]
Careful.

07:59.240 --> 08:00.514
[speaks Spanish]
Always.

08:01.800 --> 08:03.518
[engine starts]

08:23.760 --> 08:25.432
[♪♪♪]

